snippet.textDisplay:
Anthony Joshua regained his titles and to him and his fans that is all that really matters. In reality the strategy employed was far from master class and a quote from Barry McGuigan comparing AJ to Muhammad Ali is simply just ludicrous.
At best it was survival. Although AJ out pointed the lumbering Ruiz he failed time and time again to let his hands go, too afraid to use the left hooks plus combination punches because that would have drawn in Ruiz and he wanted to stay well away from that.
In addition his movement in the ring was not as fluid and relaxed as his pro observers would have you believe. AJ was both wary and cagey why else do you think the McCracken camp came up with such a strategy.
On reflection the best man of the night won. Ruiz blew a remarkable opportunity by not taking the re-match seriously. I find his remarks astounding having been an amateur boxer in my younger days. I can not believe that he did not listen to his coach and train adequately in order to take care of his weight. He also seemed all at sea with AJ on his bike, when in fact he should have been looking to cut the ring short.
In any event it was an amateur display from Ruiz and he did not by any stretch of the imagination deserve victory. Still the future of Anthony Joshua despite the Saber rattling in his corner is still very fragile and I doubt that he will ever be the undisputed Champion of the world anytime soon let a lone a truly great heavy weight ...... and at thirty I guess time really isn't on his side.

In addition his movement in the ring was not as fluid and relaxed as his pro observers would have you believe. AJ was both wary and cagey why else do you think the McCracken camp came up with such a strategy.
On reflection the best man of the night won. Ruiz blew a remarkable opportunity by not taking the re-match seriously. I find his remarks astounding having been an amateur boxer in my younger days. snippet.textDisplay:
Great that joshua brought the belts back to the 🇬🇧 and redeemed himself somewhat. It could have gone either way maybe moreso ruiz if ruiz came good and quick sharp and less hesitant this fight.

But Joshua did not show a masterclass performance. Him adhering to his tactics yes; but skill and applying pressure was far from class. Masterclass for any recent heavyweight that has been seen would be fury and wilder. Even despite that ko at the end, it was phenomenal not to even mention the two year hiatus with only 1/2 tune up fights.

Joshua utilised his jab and threw a few good combos but overall being a combination fighter and his devasting left hooks and uppercuts were not used as he did not want to close the Distance and ended up clinching or leaning towards to canvas as much as he could to allow the ref to step in.

Masterclass should be reserved for the likes of mayweather or more recently Canelo. Everyone I see seems to discuss he went the distance and kept ruiz at range and doesn’t need to brawl or go for a knockout. Agreed.
Why go brawling with a guy you’ve already had trouble with before not to mention dropping weight and the difference being 3 plus stones!

But Compare that knockout and masterclass scenario. Mayweather well pretty boy mayweather vs corralles which ended in one of the best offensive displays by mayweather with multiple knockouts in his favour but then another masterclass which was mayweather vs canelo and had zero ko from my memory but great display of counter punching and defence and offence and not afraid to close the distance and stand toe to toe showing a real MASTER OF THE CLASS.

THERES LEVELS TO THIS SHXT

snippet.textDisplay: The camera angles used by DAZN need changing to be honest. All these close up shots taken from just two cameras at each corner of the ring just makes it look amateurish. The wide shots of the ring from side on which we have become accustomed to were perfect. I understand that they are trying to innovate and modernise the production of boxing events, but changing the camera angles hasn't worked, now all of the fights just don't look right with these weird angles from basically the fighters eye level, zooming in and zooming out. Really ought to be changed back to normal because i'm sure other people have noticed it as well.
